                <note rend="inline" type="source">371.1113Keller, W. N.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-12-11T13:00:00+01:44">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1927—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. Department’s December 10, 6 p.m. The report concerning W. N. Keller, an
                    American citizen registered at the Consulate, apparently true. I made a vigorous
                    protest last Friday and the Rumanian Minister for Foreign Affairs yesterday
                    expressed regret and has assured satisfaction following a special investigation
                    being made by a representative of Department of Agriculture [<hi rend="italic"
                        >Justice</hi>] who left here yesterday. Despatch on the situation left today
                    in the pouch.<note n="14" xml:id="d647fn14">Despatch No. 508, dated Dec. 10,
                        1927, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
